            "scale": 2,
            "description": "A completed 1:2 picture graph from the Lesson appears. Visual bookend showing student's work. Clean, complete display with key visible."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "dialogue",
          "text": "You discovered something important: scaled graphs need fewer symbols. That makes them easier to read when numbers get big."
        },
        {
          "type": "dialogue",
          "text": "Next time, you'll use a scale of 5. Instead of groups of 2, you'll group by 5s. You already know how to count by 5s — that will help!"
        },
